---
title: Honey Ginger Glazed Chicken with Snow Peas and Jasmine
description: We all have a soft spot for the sticky-sweet chicken that’s a staple of takeout dinners and mall food court meals. But it’s not exactly something you would chow down on any night of the week—until now. We’re swapping out the heavy glaze for a fresh burst of ginger and a swirl of honey and soy sauce. Served with tender snow peas on a bed of jasmine rice, this recipe will give you good reason to toss the phone number for your local delivery joint.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/honey-ginger-glazed-chicken-a1fd5c7e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/honey-ginger-glazed-chicken-027d4b50.pdf
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-ginger-glazed-chicken-590c7d332310a865ef2d8892
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 510 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  saturated fat: 1.5 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 570 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring @water{2%cups} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil
in a #small pot{}. Trim any tough ends from @snow peas{8%oz}. Cut @lime{1} into wedges.
Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 2 TBSP. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.
Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{1%cup} to pot, cover, and reduce to a simmer.
Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered.

Season @chicken tenders{24%oz} all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large
drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken
in a single layer. Cook until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Remove from
pan and set aside.

In same pan, heat a large drizzle of oil over medium-low heat. Add ginger and
garlic. Toss until soft and fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Pour in @white wine vinegar{3%tbsp}
and let reduce until almost dry.

> We sent more white wine vinegar, you only need 3 TBSP.

Stir @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @honey{2%tbsp}, and
@water{1/4%cup} into pan with aromatics. Let simmer until mixture thickens to a glaze
like consistency, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> We sent more honey, you only need 2 TBSP.

Add chicken and snow peas to pan. Toss to coat in glaze. Cook until chicken is no
longer pink in center and snow peas are tender, about ~{3%minutes}. Season with salt,
pepper, and a squeeze of lime.

Divide rice between plates. Top with chicken and snow peas. Serve with lime wedges
on the side for squeezing over.